## Q2 — 6+ CC0 retro/bowling tileable pattern textures

**Recommended: generate programmatically in canvas — always CC0, always tileable, no external request.**

Six patterns implementable as `512x512` canvas draws at startup, exported to `THREE.CanvasTexture` with `wrapS = wrapT = THREE.RepeatWrapping`:

| # | Name | Canvas recipe |
|---|------|--------------|
| 1 | Atomic Starburst | Gold 8-point star + circle rings on navy bg |
| 2 | Bowling Pins | White pin silhouettes offset row pattern on coral bg |
| 3 | Argyle Diamond | Navy/cream/coral diagonal diamonds with hairline crosses |
| 4 | 50s Polka Dot | Large cream dots on navy with small coral accent dots |
| 5 | Lane Chevrons | Alternating navy/gold chevron rows (bowling lane arrow motif) |
| 6 | Atomic Bowtie | Repeating hourglass/bowtie shapes, classic cocktail-lounge motif |

Fallback CDN if canvas draw is skipped: `https://www.transparenttextures.com/` (CC0, many seamless patterns via direct PNG URL, e.g. `https://www.transparenttextures.com/patterns/argyle.png`). Also `https://subtlepatterns.com/` (CC0, zip download).

**Decision for demo-builder: generate all 6 in canvas at module init — zero network dependency, zero license risk.**

