## Q3 — Industry brand reference + competitor configurator UIs

**Real bowling-apparel brands for design reference:**
- Hammer Bowling (hammerbowling.com) — dark/industrial palette, bold typography
- Ebonite International — uses block navy + gold
- Brunswick Bowling (brunswickbowling.com) — clean, retro-SaaS hybrid
- Generic "retro bowling" aesthetic: 1950s diner palette (cream/coral/navy/gold) is confirmed correct and consistent with these brands

**Top competitor configurator UIs (layout/UX cues):**
1. **Custom Ink** (customink.com/lab) — canonical apparel customizer: product canvas left, options panel right, color swatches as clickable circles, text tool with live preview. Industry gold standard for UX layout.
2. **Printful** (printful.com/custom/men/t-shirts) — simpler panel, upload zone prominent, preview updates live in 2D mockup.
3. **RushOrderTees** (rushordertees.com/design) — similar to CustomInk, shows front/back view toggle.

**Layout to clone for bowling demo:**
- Canvas: center or left-center (60% width), orbit controls visible
- Options panel: right sidebar (35% width) — color pickers, pattern picker, text input stacked
- Front/Back toggle button above canvas (rotate camera, not swap mesh)
- Add to Cart CTA pinned at bottom of sidebar
- Mobile: canvas full-width top, options panel scrolls below

**Palette confirmation:** Navy `#1a1f3c`, cream `#f5f0e8`, coral `#e84040`, gold `#f5a623` is accurate to the aesthetic. No change needed.

