## Q4 — Three.js/r3f customizer reference implementation

**Canonical pattern to follow:** The Vercel AI SDK shirt demo (github.com/vercel-labs/generative-ui — the 3D shirt configurator from their 2023 Next.js Conf demo) is the most-cited r3f shirt customizer. It uses:
- `@react-three/fiber` Canvas with `<OrbitControls>` from drei
- `<Decal>` from drei for texture overlays (logo/image placement on mesh surface)
- Zustand store for customization state
- `useTexture` hook for loading textures

For **applied patterns as repeating texture**: set `material.map` directly via `useTexture` or `new THREE.TextureLoader().load(url)`, then `texture.wrapS = texture.wrapT = THREE.RepeatWrapping; texture.repeat.set(3,3)`. In r3f: pass as `map` prop on `<meshStandardMaterial>`.

For **per-material color**: each mesh group gets its own `<meshStandardMaterial color={zustandStore.bodyColor}>`. React re-renders on store change, Three.js updates on next frame.

For **live upload**: `URL.createObjectURL(file)` → pass URL to `useTexture` (or `new THREE.TextureLoader().load(url)`) — works in browser, GC on revoke.

